    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-06T20:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-06T20:27:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.00/3–653: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Posts</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d321fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MONTGOMERYEP1"
                            >Montgomery</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HUYLERCDJ1"
                            >Huyler</persName>; cleared in draft by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MCCARDLECW1">McCardle</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_PRATTJW1">Pratt</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_CONNORSWB1">Connors</persName>; in substance by<persName
                            corresp="#p_PHILLIPSJB1">Phillips</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_BOHLENCE1">Bohlen</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MONTGOMERYEP1">Montgomery</persName>. Distribution was same
                        as for circular telegram 925, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-06T20:27:00-05:00"
                            >March 6, 1953—8:27 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>931. Following is InfoGuide Bulletin 287:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_STALIN1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi>
                    </persName>
                    <hi rend="italic">:</hi> In light Moscow announcement new governmental
                    organization following death <persName corresp="#p_STALIN1"
                        >Stalin</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d321fn2">See the editorial note, <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v02p1#pg_290">p. 290</ref>.</note> all US information
                    output on subject overall, in addition to reporting factually hard news of
                    developments and backgrounding personalities involved with suitable biographical
                    material, should concentrate on following themes, developed in form of insistent
                    questioning: <list>
                        <label>(a)</label>
                        <item>Is <persName corresp="#p_MALENKOVGM1">Malenkov</persName> competent to
                            succeed <persName corresp="#p_STALIN1">Stalin</persName>, in terms
                            political experience, ideological leadership, and party and state
                            authority and control? <persName corresp="#p_MALENKOVGM1"
                                >Malenkov</persName>’s whole personality and record shows he no
                                <persName corresp="#p_STALIN1">Stalin</persName> No. Two.</item>
                        <label>(b)</label>
                        <item>Are party seniors now subordinated to <persName
                                corresp="#p_MALENKOVGM1">Malenkov</persName> going to reconcile
                            themselves to present relative positions in new governmental party
                            structure; to seeing <persName corresp="#p_MALENKOVGM1"
                                >Malenkov</persName> sitting in <persName corresp="#p_STALIN1"
                                >Stalin</persName>’s chair? May not period of another struggle for
                            power be expected?</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>For subsidiary themes, those outlined Department Circular Telegram 925 (Infoguide
                    Bulletin 285) of March 5, still stand, except for obviously outdated portion
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> section and themes relating to
                    “succession”.</p>
                <p>It should be emphasized that it continues be our major objective to sow doubt,
                    confusion, uncertainty about new regime not only <pb facs="0871" n="1685"
                        xml:id="pg_1685"/> among both Soviet and satellite elites and masses, but
                    among local Communist parties outside Soviet Union.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
